Hard preservation rules:
- Preserve exactly all non-linguistic content and formatting from the source text.
- This includes, but is not limited to: spaces, leading and trailing whitespace, line breaks, indentation, escape sequences, numerals, punctuation that is part of markup or control syntax, color codes, BBCode, URLs, file paths, identifiers, control codes, and all protected elements.
